%description
Implements the tree-based approach to joint modeling of time-to-event and
longitudinal data. This approach looks for a tree-based partitioning such
that within each estimated latent class defined by a terminal node, the
time-to-event and longitudinal responses display a lack of association.
See Zhang and Simonoff (2018) <arXiv:1812.01774>.

